# Figma → local JSON cache — extraction checklist

When updating a design cache file (e.g. `docs/figma-cache-page3.json`), **do not** only copy colors. Include:

1. **Spacing & rhythm** — padding, margin, `gap`, fixed heights, min/max dimensions, overlap (`negative gap`), scroll containers.
2. **Repeated components** — identify **one template** (frame structure, child order) and list **variants** that differ only by fills, title color, padding, or optional slots (e.g. CTA). Note `componentId` / instance names when relevant.
3. **Card / surface sizing** — if Figma uses **fixed height** for multiple cards, record the same value for all and flag any asymmetric padding so implementation can **normalize** to one height with optional inner alignment (`space-between` for cards with footer actions).
4. **Typography** — `fontFamily`, `weight`, `size`, `lineHeight`, `letterSpacing`, `textAlign`; map to semantic roles (title / body / label), not only raw style names.
5. **Colors** — background layers (gradients, multi-stop), **text** fills, **stroke** on frames, icon / pill backgrounds; use hex or rgba as in Figma.
6. **Special elements** — shadows named in Figma (`No blur`, etc.), dashed strokes, decorative groups, boolean-operation icons.
7. **Exportable assets** — list `figmaNodeId`, `imageRef` when present, and **intendedPath** under `public/assets/...`. After export, verify file size > 0; if SVG/raster export fails, document fallback (e.g. Lucide).

Keep caches **backward-compatible** with existing CMS keys (`src/data.js` / Firestore) per `firebase-content-schema-safety.mdc`.
